Upon power up the clock screen may not be displayed. The screen is considered the 
main screen and will be the starting point for all programming.  
 
Press the DOWN key to scroll until the clock screen is shown. 
 
To enter into program mode press ESC once. Arrow down to desired selection and press 
OK.  
 
 To set clock, arrow down to SET and press OK. CLOCK will appear. Press 
OK. SET CLOCK will then appear. Press OK again.  Use LEFT and 
RIGHT arrow keys to maneuver around and the UP and DOWN keys to 
change setting. Once complete press OK. To get back to main screen press ESC 
three times. 
 
EXAMPLES: 
 
TH 10:30  =  10:30 AM THURSDAY 
 
FR 23:15  =  11:15 PM FRIDAY 
 
MO 13:30 = 1:30 P MONDAY 
 
To view inputs, at the main screen (clock showing) press the RIGHT arrow key. To 
return to main screen press LEFT arrow key. 
To view outputs, at the main screen (clock showing) press the RIGHT arrow key 
twice. To return to main screen press LEFT arrow key twice.

9000-4r3 Operation Description (1-4 Fields) 
NORMAL OPERATION 
 
There is 2-minute (non-settable) power-up delay before the pumps are allowed to run and the field 
dose valves are allowed to open. 
o During the 2-minute power-up delay, the filter valves and the field flush valve will open for 1 
minute. 
 
After the 2-minute power-up delay, if the WIDE ANGLE PUMP ON-OFF PERMISSIVE float is 
activated and the pump has been activated for 1 minute, the fields will begin dosing in sequence 
starting with field 1: 
 
A pump will turn on 
 
Filter valve will open 
 
Filter valve will close the set field flush time after pump turns on (set by parameter B3) 
 
Field dose valve will open 
 
Pump will shut off after the set field dose time (set by parameters B101-B104) 
 
Field dose valve will remain open for the set field dose drain time after pump turns off (set 
by parameter B109-B112)  
 
The filter valve will open for the set filter drain time after pump turns off (set by parameter 
B4) 
 
Field flush valve will open for the set field flush drain time after pump turns off (set by 
parameter B6) 
 
Pump will remain off for the set off time during normal operation (set by parameter B1) 
 
After a set number of pumps starts (set by parameter B8), the next time the pump starts the field 
flush valve will open for the set time for normal operations (set by parameter B5)
